Redshift:
=========

- Data warehouse in aws
- optimised for analytics.
- used for reporting purpose.
- OLAP not for OLTP.
- column based storage.
- It has leader node to which we can submit our queries.
- data is stored in compute node.
- any jdbc connection to postgres can be used for connecting to redshift. eg(tableau, amazon quicksight)
- using amazon quicksight we can query redshift, DynamaDB etc.,
- spectrum
    - query unstructured data stored in s3 buckets
    - query exabytes of data in few minutes.
- scalable.
- low cost($1000 per tb per year)
